This paper is about a new model for reinforcement learning that is both interpretable and verifiable. The paper discusses the use of decision trees and mixture of experts to achieve this goal. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses safety-critical settings, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper mentions the use of automated theorem provers, which could place it in the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
